and so like a potter manipulating basic clay and turning it into beautiful pots, he was able to transform harmful action and substances into something positive and beneficial. guru rinpoche's special association with bhutan began when he traveled to the town now known as jakar at the invitation of a local king to subjugate negative forces. the mission was a success, and from this encounter buddhism spread throughout the land. a body print of the great sage exists to this day at kurjey lhakhang in jakar, and he is also associated with many other sacred sites in bhutan, with perhaps 